HEADWORD: Subversive
<hw>Sub*ver"sive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>subversif</ets>.]</ety> <def>Tending to subvert; having a tendency
to overthrow and ruin.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Lying is a vice <qex>subversive</qex> of the very ends and design
of conversation.</q> <rj><qau>Rogers.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Subvert</ent>⟦br⟧
